aa76809 seems to be a workaround. Requesting Nashorn compatibility mode activates NASHORN_HOST_ACCESS which contains the Long ⇒ String conversion as identified by Samuel. By calling
b.put("polyglot.js.allowHostAccess", true);
after that one replaces the Nashorn compatibility host access with HostAccess.ALL switching back to the behavior of the engine as of GraalVM 19.3.x. CCing @iamstolis
